subject: Are Octopuses Aliens? Yes, and We Can Prove It!
text:
Scientists have recently analyzed a full octopus genome and found that their DNA is unlike anything else on Earth. With lots of genes packed densely together and genes that would normally group together being spread out through the genome, they have said that the octopus is basically an alien. Of course, anyone who's seen a sci-fi movie could have told you that just by looking them.

subject: The Oldest Living Cat Recently Turned 26-Years-Old!
text:
Corduroy, born on August 1st, 1989, holds the Guinness World Record for being the oldest cat alive. He loves mice, sharp cheddar and simply being a cat. 



Even at 26 he keeps a busy schedule roaming his owner's 160-acre ranch in Oregon. Somehow he still finds the time to nap regularly. 


Via Guinness World Records

subject: A Cat Survived a Devastating Fire With Only Singed Whisker or Two
text:
A family in California thought they lost everything in a forest fire that swept through their home and forced them to evacuate the area for five days. Their cat, Ruthie Rosemary, panicked and ran away during the evacuation and they thought she was lost to them. 



The fire was so hot that it melted the aluminum on vehicles that the family left behind but miraculously, Ruthie Rosemary came out nearly unscathed. A few curled whiskers and eyebrows are all the evidence of the cat withstanding the fire. It's unclear where she hid from the fire or how she made it out alive but her owners are obviously happy she did.

subject: A Bear and a Wolf Formed an Unlikely Friendship Worthy of a Disney Movie
text:

Normally, wolves and bears compete for resources but it appears that these two are happy to stick together. It's possible that all they have is each other. They have been seen playing together and even sharing meals.
